    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-05-04T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-05-04T05:00:00-05:00" n="447"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d447">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4331: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-05-04T18:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1922—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 4—1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>197. Department’s no. 108 of May 2. U.S.S. <hi rend="italic">Huron</hi> is due
                    off Taku at 7 a.m tomorrow. Strauss has given orders for landing of 150 marines
                    with machine guns at Tientsin by tug. U.S.S. <hi rend="italic">Wilmington</hi>
                    is under orders to proceed to Taku.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
